<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36109k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36109k">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36109k"> 109(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Damn me I burn</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">With a cold-hearted barbarity that mars his undoubted claims as a statesman and general, he <font color="green">[Cromwell]</font> records how some of the vanquished fled to the steeple of a church, which was immediately, by his orders, set on fire. He was near enough to note the cries of his victims, for he heard one poor wretch say, &ldquo;<mark>Damn me, I burn, I burn.</mark>&rdquo; <small> D.A. Chart, <a name="DACD" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#DACD"><cite title="source">The Story of Dublin</cite></a> (1907) 81</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
